 <p><center><IMG SRC="http://kilroyc.globalhelix.com/adex_nametag.jpg"></center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uadexxeda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adex Xeda</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://kilroyc.globalhelix.com/adex_icon.jpg height=30 width=30 BORDER=0> at: 5/25/01 7:52:00 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uadexxeda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adex Xeda</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://kilroyc.globalhelix.com/adex_icon.jpg height=30 width=30 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Swift</BR>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 196<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/25/01 7:57:25 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://kilroyc.globalhelix.com/adex_portrait.jpg width = 136 height = 267 ></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Prince and King in Chardok</span><hr size=1> When my folks kill the prince we fight our way to the outside of the castle. <br>
<br>
We invis up and move inside to the corner a ways down the hall from the prince. From that corner we drop invis and AoE any mobs that aggro. After a bit of this hallway cleaning we send a monk into the prince's room to pull the prince and friends out then FD. We pick off the stragglers as they return inside. Eventually the prince gets isolated. Once the prince is alone we charge the prince room and kill him.<br>
<br>
<br>
From there we invis up again and walk around to the other side of the hallway and move into the safe room opposite the prince door on the other side of the hallway. From here we AoE fight our way down the library and then into the Herbalist room. Herbalist room has 4-5 spawn points. We beat down these spawn points and send the pull team down to the king area to FD and isolate the king from his guards. Once the king is isolated we actually pull the king up into the herbalist room. I like fighting in the herb room because you don't get any back pops on you like you do when you're in the hallway that leads to the king/queen. Also if you do have a bust the CR is easy if you parked a rogue and cleric in the safe spot. <p><center><IMG SRC="http://kilroyc.globalhelix.com/adex_nametag.jpg"></center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uadexxeda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adex Xeda</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://kilroyc.globalhelix.com/adex_icon.jpg height=30 width=30 BORDER=0> at: 5/25/01 7:59:03 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udaenerysoftargaryen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daenerys of Targaryen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/25/01 7:58:06 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.drakonblayde.net/gfx/tarsig.jpg WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Prince and King in Chardok</span><hr size=1> Nm, didnt read subject <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
